 in combination with NSAIDs. Patients receiving oral bisphosphonates should be closely monitored for the development of gastrointestinal toxicity and advised to immediately report potential signs and symptoms such as severe abdominal pain, nausea, vomiting, diarrhea, loss of appetite, dizziness, lightheadedness, and/or black, tarry stools. Patients receiving intravenous formulations of bisphosphonates should have renal function and serum electrolytes closely monitored.', 'Synergism', 'Caution is advised if bisphosphonates are prescribed in combination with NSAIDs.', 'Moderate', 'pharmacodynamic', NULL, 'https://ddinter2.scbdd.com/server/interact/34939/', '', 'Chondroitin sulfate, Esomeprazole, Glucosamine', 'Vosoritide, Denosumab, Cholecalciferol, Burosumab, Romosozumab', 1767369485);
